        "x-mint": {
          "metadata": {
            "tag": "beta"
          }
        },
        "summary": "Create an experiment",
        "description": "Create a new experiment. Empty experiments are not allowed.\n\nExperiments are composed of \"runs\". Each experiment run (JSON object)\nmust include an `example_id` field that corresponds to an example in\nthe dataset, and a `output` field that contains the task's output for\nthe example (the input).\n\nPayload Requirements\n- The `name` must be unique within the target dataset\n- Provide at least one run in `experiment_runs`.\n- Each run must include:\n  - `example_id` -- the ID of an existing example in the dataset/version\n  - `output` -- model/task output for that example\n  - You may include any additional fields per run that can be used for\n  analysis or filtering. For exampple: `model`, `latency_ms`,\n  `temperature`, `prompt`, `tool_calls`, etc.\n\n<Note>This endpoint is in beta, read more [here](https://arize.com/docs/ax/rest-reference#api-version-stages).</Note>\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "$ref": "#/components/requestBodies/CreateExperimentRequestBody"
        },
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Experiment"
          },
          "400": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/BadRequest"
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Unauthorized"
          },
          "403": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Forbidden"
          },
          "409": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Conflict"
          },
          "422": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/BadRequest"
          },
          "429": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/RateLimitExceeded"
          }
        }
      }
    },
