    "/v2/resource-restrictions": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Resource Restrictions"
        ],
        "operationId": "resource_restrictions_create",
        "summary": "Restrict a resource",
        "description": "Mark a resource as restricted. Only space admins or users with the RESOURCE_RESTRICT\npermission can perform this action. Idempotent.\n\n**Payload Requirements**\n- `resource_id`: The ID for the resource. \n  Only `project` resources are currently supported. Other resource types are not currently supported and will return 400.\n\n**Valid example**\n```json\n{ \"resource_id\": \"TW9kZWw6MTIxOmFCY0Q=\" }\n```\n\n**Invalid example**\n```json\n{ \"resource_id\": \"Not a project ID\" }\n```\nReturns 400 \u2014 only Project / Model IDs are accepted \n\n<Warning>This endpoint is in alpha, read more [here](https://arize.com/docs/ax/rest-reference#api-version-stages).</Warning>\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": [
                  "resource_id"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "resource_id": {
                    "description": "The ID of the resource to restrict",
                    "allOf": [
                      {
                        "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Id"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                },
                "additionalProperties": false
              },
              "example": {
                "resource_id": "TW9kZWw6MTIxOmFCY0Q="
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/ResourceRestrictionResponse"
          },
          "400": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/BadRequest"
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Unauthorized"
          },
          "403": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Forbidden"
          },
          "404": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/NotFound"
          },
          "429": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/RateLimitExceeded"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/v2/resource-restrictions/{resource_id}": {
      "delete": {
        "tags": [
          "Resource Restrictions"
        ],
        "operationId": "resource_restrictions_delete",
        "summary": "Unrestrict a resource",
        "description": "Remove restriction from a resource. Removing a restriction from a resource means that roles bound at other levels of the hierarchy (space, org, account) can grant access to the resource. Returns 404 if the resource is not restricted.\n\n<Warning>This endpoint is in alpha, read more [here](https://arize.com/docs/ax/rest-reference#api-version-stages).</Warning>\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/ResourceIdPathParam"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "204": {
            "description": "Resource restriction deleted"
          },
          "400": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/BadRequest"
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Unauthorized"
          },
          "403": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Forbidden"
          },
          "404": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/NotFound"
          },
          "429": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/RateLimitExceeded"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/v2/role-bindings": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Role Bindings"
        ],
        "operationId": "role_bindings_create",
        "x-mint": {
          "metadata": {
            "tag": "alpha"
          }
        },
        "summary": "Create a role binding",
        "description": "Create a new role binding that assigns a role to a user on a resource.\n\n**Payload Requirements**\n- `role_id`, `user_id`, `resource_type`, and `resource_id` are required.\n- `resource_type` must be `SPACE` or `PROJECT`.\n- `resource_id` must be a global ID for the selected `resource_type`.\n- Only one binding per user and resource is allowed. If the target user\n  already has any binding on the resource, the request returns\n  `409 Conflict`.\n- System-managed fields (`id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) are returned\n  by the server and are rejected on input.\n\n**Valid example**\n```json\n{\n  \"role_id\": \"Um9sZToxOlY0S2E=\",\n  \"user_id\": \"VXNlcjoxOmxQZzI=\",\n  \"resource_type\": \"PROJECT\",\n  \"resource_id\": \"TW9kZWw6MTpGdmxM\"\n}\n```\n\n**Invalid example**\n```json\n{\n  \"role_id\": \"Um9sZToxOlY0S2E=\",\n  \"user_id\": \"VXNlcjoxOmxQZzI=\",\n  \"resource_type\": \"PROJECT\",\n  \"resource_id\": \"U3BhY2U6MTp1Rk4x\"\n}\n```\nThis fails because `resource_id` must encode a `PROJECT` ID when\n`resource_type` is `PROJECT`.\n\nUse `PATCH /v2/role-bindings/{binding_id}` to change the assigned role\nfor an existing binding.\n\n<Warning>This endpoint is in alpha, read more [here](https://arize.com/docs/ax/rest-reference#api-version-stages).</Warning>\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "$ref": "#/components/requestBodies/CreateRoleBindingRequestBody"
        },
        "responses": {
          "201": {
